<event name="CRYSTAL_SANCTUARY" unique="true">
	<preventQuest/>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_CRYSTALCONSTRUCTION" planet="NONE"/>
	<text>You've discovered a massive Crystalline society, well furnished and protected. In the center is a small village surrounding a massive contraption... it looks like a gateway of some sort?</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Investigate the gateway.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The contraption seems to resemble a much larger version of the Waystone, the device that the Crystalline people used to seal off their old homeworlds. As you approach, a massive Crystalline cruiser approaches, its weapons aiming straight at you!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_CRYSTAL_BOSS" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Uh oh...</text>
				<event>
					<text>A ceremoniously painted purple Crystal stands before you, far taller than those in the background. "I am Empress Dianesh Kryel. You... are a foreigner, and foreigners are unwelcome. The Federation has given us its aid, and for that we are grateful. But we are no longer in need of the Federation, and you need nothing of us. We shall negotiate terms."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Negotiate what?</text>
						<event>
							<text>"The terms on which you leave this place. Your presence here is not sanctioned. I know people like you. Ambassador Ruwen has told me the stories. You are barbarians, murderers. Renegades like you were the ones who first stole our home from us. And I refuse to allow such things to transpire again. I will satisfy whatever vain desires you might have to ensure you leave and never return. My people do not want you here."</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Request a weapon.</text>
								<event>
									<text>Dianesh gestures for a small transport ship to approach and deliver a specialized Crystal weapon. "We have met your demands, now you will abide by ours and leave." You figure it's best not to press further and follow their instructions.</text>
									<weapon name="GIFTLIST_CRYSTAL"/>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Request crew.</text>
								<event>
									<text>Dianesh gestures for a small transport ship to approach. It delivers a Crystalline prisoner, who eagerly joins your crew as long as it brings an end to their sentence. "We have met your demands, now you will abide by ours and leave." You figure it's best not to press further and follow their instructions.</text>
									<crewMember amount="1" class="sentinel"/>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Request repairs.</text>
								<event>
									<text>Dianesh gestures for a support ship to come by and give a full repair. "We have met your demands, now you will abide by ours and leave." You figure it's best not to press further and follow their instructions.</text>
									<damage amount="-45"/>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>We did not come here to harm you. We are not as bad as you say.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Oh but you see, only by making such claims do you prove your intentions. Were you of true heart, you would have already left. But you persist. Persistence is a threat. And my people do not take kindly to threats." You try to protest further but Dianesh will not listen. She waves and her cruiser moves forth to strike you down. Maybe this doesn't have to end in bloodshed though, but the Crystals aren't going to listen so easily.</text>
									<ship hostile="true"/>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the place.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Diving so deep into a Crystalline city is generally not a good idea. You distance yourself from the planet.</text>
			<choice>
